<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail, a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

[1]
Date: Fri 26 Jan 2007
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: WRL FMD Monthly Typing Reports, December 2006 [edited]
<http://www.iah.bbsrc.ac.uk/primary_index/current_research/virus/Picornaviridae/Aphthovirus/fmd_serotyping/2006/FMD2006-12.pdf>

[In the posting "Foot & mouth disease (type A) - Jordan: OIE" of 16
Jan 2007, we included the following queries:
Has the outbreak in Amman, which reportedly started on 15 Oct 2006
and confirmed 19 Dec 2006, remained solitary?
Has there been any spread?"

No response has been obtained so far. The following data, which have
become available from the WRL for FMD website [Pirbright, UK --
source URL above] on 24 Jan 2007, indicate infection of 3 animals. It
would help to note whether they have been sampled in one or more
locations. - Mod.AS]


Sample I.D / Animal / Collection Date / VI/ELISA* / RT-PCR / Final report
-----------------------------------------------
JOR 1/2006 / Sheep / 06.12.06 / NVD** / Negative / NVD**
JOR 2/2006 / Cattle / 06.12.06 / A / Positive / A
JOR 3/2006 / Cattle / 06.12.06 / A / Positive / A
JOR 4/2006 / Cattle / 06.12.06 / A / Positive / A
JOR 5/2006 / Sheep / 06.12.06 / O / Positive / O
JOR 6/2006 / Cattle / 06.12.06 / O / Positive / O
JOR 7/2006 / Sheep / 06.12.06 / O / Positive / O

*FMDV serotype identified following virus isolation in cell culture
and antigen detection ELISA
** no FMD, swine vesicular disease or vesicular stomatitis virus detected

